			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Soloing PoFear<a name="36103"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 23 04 8:59 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Selos and invis then zone in.  Head west to zone wall then north along it to the NW corner and FM just north of the flame wall(east of NW corner).  From there just chant or swarm(used CoB) down all the mobs in the NW corner(I had 5 or 6) then start on the temple.  Simple range agro will get you a number of mobs so just FM if you get too many.  Shissar is the only annoying mob, as it doesn't seem to reset after FM so if need be park him northeast of the temple.  The whip only drops off the warriors, the knights are sks.  I got mine on the first warrior then invited another bard up and stayed around to kill the rest of them without seeing a 2nd whip drop.  I just used a thurg potion to get out, you don't need to splurge on insta-gate unless they didn't change Ire's spawning.
<br />

<br />
I never had a problem with Ire but i only needed to kill 2 scarelings.  I thought they'd <a target="_new" href="http://www.eqdiva.com/Forums/ShowPost.aspx?PostID=32523#34542&quot; target=_new">changed</a> the spawn so a nonagro imp spawns first and must be killed before ire pops but don't quote me on that.
<br />

<br />
For spells just use your normal kite setup with PoV.  The only time anything landed on me was after i got hit with tash but i still resisted a number of spells before cureing it.  Mobs run on low health too.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
