				<td colspan="2"><span>i would wait for lvl 65, FM and about 100-150 Magic resist or higher to be safe.
<br />

<br />
my experience in soloing the whip in pof was quite funny. I did the usual, when in ran to the north west corner and FM. I killed all the warriors in the temple, there were lots of adds each pull included that annoying evil eye who kept dispelling my selo.
<br />

<br />
I guess i wasn't very patient, so i checked the zone to make sure non of the DT (death touch) mobs were up, and then i proceed to kite the ENTIRE zone hoping to get all the warriors, and you know what...
<br />

<br />
it actually wasn't bad at all
<br />

<br />
as i said my patient were running thin since i solo in fear quite a few times killing the temple and getting nothing, so after i killed the wandering warriors i actually got one to drop... here is the funny part. I got so excite i took my time looting the whip *mistake here* that got me killed BUT i did loot it.
<br />

<br />
I got a necro to come in summon corpse res stone me and we both gated.
<br />

<br />
2 days later got my EPIC
<br />

<br />
The key thing here is lvl 65, FM and resist
<br />

<br />
FM: To clear aggro if you can't take the heat. To tell you the truth... if none of the DT mobs are up (and that zerker epic imp though i didn't encounter him), you can kite the entire zone seriously.... HOWEVER see comments below
<br />

<br />
lvl 65: The reason i would push this is because of spell casting level... these mobs are lvl 50s and if you are high level you WILL be almost completely immune to their spells (excpet dispell)
<br />

<br />
Resist: To be even more resistant to their spell, some of them do root like that evil eye's pet .... and if you DO kite the entire zone some of them will NUKE you. But i am lvl 65 with resist and it didn't hurt they are too low level to spell hurt me</span></td>
