				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Soloing PoFear<a name="39917"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 14 04 7:03 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, I grabbed a few friends and headed to PoFear tonight for my whip.  
<br />

<br />
Group was Me (65 Bard), 65 SK, 65 Chanter, 65 Druid, and eventually 65 Cleric twoboxed by Chanter.
<br />

<br />
Sk invised, zoned in, ran to west wall.  Picked up some aggro from the undead, trained to NW corner, FD'd np.  The rest of us go in and head west, but the same undead mob aggros, I made it to the NW corner, FM'd and was fine.  Me and SK started kiting, but the chanter and druid both managed to gate out.  It was around that time that the first DT from Fright went off and killed the SK.  After that is was pretty much chaos lol.  I was fine for a long long time, I got all my buffs dispelled and got knocked down below 50% health once or twice, had to Fade only a few times, when druid or chanter trained me later.  I died from the second DT and had some trouble getting past that undead mob to get my body back.  I finally just pulled the see invis mobs to the sk, he took aggro, i looted my body and started kiting again.  I eventually ended up kiting just about the whole NW end of the zone while the rest of the group finally performed the CR on multipul corpses in the SOUTHWest corner.
<br />

<br />
There was only one undead mob between the zone in and the west wall.  The Sk trained it away and kited the mobs that aggro'd while the invised chanter, druid, and now cleric ran a little south down the wall where no mobs saw invis.  He FD'd to clear aggro and summoned bodies to there.
<br />

<br />
Once they were rezzed and had the SW corner secure I only had 2 mobs left, I faded, invised and made it to them without any aggro.  We killed 4 Amy Wars and the 4th one dropped the whip for me =)
<br />

<br />
I did die a second time tho right after we killed the 2nd Amy War from the 3rd DT.
<br />

<br />
So, just to let everyone know it may be easier to break camp in the South West corner, but you probabley won't know untill you try.  If none of the DT mobs are up you don't have to worry about dying by default.
<br />

<br />
Soloing this zone is very doable, but also time consuming, hand cramping, boring, and a pain in the arse lol.  The more ppl you can get to do this with you the better imo.  Much faster and more efficient.  
<br />

<br />
I agree that lvl 65 is definatley a good level to do it due to spell resists. PoV was a big help not only for the resists but the DS never hurts when the mobs do get to beat you.  The mobs don't hit all that hard, most hits were under 100, but 100 X 12 mobs hurts a little bit after you've been dispelled (wich is vertually unpreventable).
<br />

<br />
You can't bind outside of PoFear unless you are a caster and can bind yourself, so PoK is probabley your best bet for binding. =)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
