			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Soloing PoFear<a name="43186"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 31 04 12:00 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Someone mentioned this, and a Bard from Flowers of Happiness posted a cool guide thats actually available in the Epic section on EQDiva I believe.
<br />

<br />
Zone in while invisible and selo'd.  Hit the wall and run north to the Fire Castle.  Park your a$ behind the castle at the zone wall and Fade off aggro, making sure nothing is on you.
<br />

<br />
You're at camp.  While facing the Fire Castle, you should see no mobs on your right along the wall and cube-blobs and horses to your left, out of aggro range. 
<br />

<br />
First pulls are easy.  Pulse Psalm of Veeshan and head toward the northwest corner of the castle, running along the castle wall until you see a casting message or get a spell hits/resists on you.  Run back to camp, keep Psalm up.
<br />

<br />
Sometimes, a single mob would come and I would just chant it.  Other times, a few came out (warriors, knights, eyes) and I would chant them all in order of eye, knight, then warrior.  Occassionally, more than 3 or 4 came out and I would pull the mobs along the wall, target a warrior, snare him, and Fade to get him single.  Your call here... It's a pain in the a$ when you die alone here, so I went the cautious route and chanted singles as often as possible.
<br />

<br />
Your safe spot along the wall is great for medding up, and I always preferred to pull with atleast 2 Fades in me.  I beleive it took me 8 warriors to get the whip, about 2 hours of my time including figuring out how it worked.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
