			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Good idea to start North East<a name="47238"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 20 04 11:03 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Howdy.  65, 36 AA Bard here.
<br />

<br />
Well, I just completed my 1st solo Fear trip.  I did it with no buffs, ~2800 HPs, 129 MR (270 with Chorus).  I was rather nervous to start, but, it was really pretty darn easy, but NO WHIP DROPPED.
<br />

<br />
Fright and Terror were both up.  CT was not.  I cleared the Amy Temple, and got a couple wanderers, but didnt want to press my luck by getting to close to a Golem.  I never really ventured any farther west than Amy temple and only grabbed one Amy Warrior from the south of the temple near the TT house.
<br />

<br />
I seloed, invised and zoned in.  Headed to West wall, and then ran North to NW corner, then ran to just north of Fire wall and faded.
<br />

<br />
I found I didnt need to twist Resist song with 129 MR.  Everything seemed to bounce of me.  The Glare Lords to like to remove your Selos, but with Run3, it wasnt much of an issue.  I resisted I think every Glare Lord pet spell, Earth something or other.
<br />

<br />
After fooling with NW corner roamers, I stepped into the Fire Ring and pulled.  Using the NW corner seems pretty easy, with the occasional add.
<br />

<br />
I chanted down a couple Scarlings.  I only got shadowstepped once.  I am guessing its a range based thing?  No big deal.  One scarling death did spawn the Enraged Imp.  Indifferent to me, but he liked to add to my swarm when I was chanting down his buddies.
<br />

<br />
Not wanting to kill the Enraged Imp, I ran him south a little and then back north and faded.  The Enraged Imp seemed to stay where ever I &quot;parked&quot; him.  The enraged eventually depsawned.
<br />

<br />
I chanted down a TT while dragging a Glare Lord behind.  No big deal.  My Selos was dropped a lot, but, wasn't a problem with Run3.
<br />

<br />
I didn't want to fool with the Wraith of a Shissar (it tried to cast a lot Stone something on me), and it added on every pull, so I dragged the mess of mobs south, then ran north and faded.  The wraith seemed to stay in place.  At least for a bit.
<br />

<br />
The FrightFingers were the worst, if I happened to let my resists fall, they nuked me for 500+.  So, I just ran around with heal and resist song until they seemed to have spent their load and then chanted them down. I think the lowest I got on health was around 46%, and I just ran around and sang resists/heal.  Most of the time I was at 100%.
<br />

<br />
I got a couple Heat Bloods on me.  I guess from Amy Knights.
<br />

<br />
Nothing summoned me.  It's been 3+ years since I took a step into Fear, so couldn't remember if they did or not.
<br />

<br />
On average, with my DoTs doing 134 a tick, it took me ~4 minutes to 3dot twist a mob down.  I could of been more aggressive, but, I kept some utility spells up as this was my 1st time.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
